#: chemotools.projection._orthogonal_pls.OrthogonalPLS:1 of
msgid ""
"A transformer that removes variation in X that is orthogonal to the "
"target y using Orthogonal Projection to Latent Structures (OPLS) [1]_."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._orthogonal_pls.OrthogonalPLS:4 of
msgid ""
"OPLS extends PLS by explicitly separating X into predictive variation, "
"correlated with y, and orthogonal variation, unrelated to y. At each "
"iteration, a predictive weight vector is estimated using the PLS "
"criterion (maximizing covariance between X and y). Scores and loadings "
"are then computed, and the loading vector is decomposed into a component "
"aligned with the predictive weight and a component orthogonal to it. The "
"orthogonal component defines an orthogonal score vector, which is used to"
" deflate X."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._orthogonal_pls.OrthogonalPLS:12 of
msgid ""
"This procedure is repeated to remove multiple orthogonal components while"
" retaining the predictive structure. Multivariate targets are supported "
"via decomposition of the cross-covariance matrix."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._orthogonal_pls.OrthogonalPLS:16 of
msgid ""
"The transformer returns X with orthogonal variation removed, preserving "
"the original number of features."
msgstr ""

